// make_final_table.cpp
// Standalone C++11 (STL only) port of make_final_table.R
//
// Build:
//   g++ -std=c++11 -O2 -o make_final_table make_final_table.cpp
//
// Run (same argument order as R):
//   ./make_final_table <blat.psl> <fusion_info.reads> <gene_counts> <trans_table>
//                      <mitelman> <cosmic> <cosmic_tier> <gtex>
//                      <gapmin> <exclude_csv> <MIN_REASSIGNMENT_BASE_DIFF> <output>
//
// Notes:
// - Assumes tab-delimited inputs like the R script.
// - PSL is expected to be standard 21-column BLAT PSL (no header).
// - The annotation table is expected to have columns used by the R script:
//     chrom, txStart, txEnd, exonStarts, exonEnds, exonFrames, name2, strand, (and possibly chromStart/chromEnd).
//   If txStart/txEnd missing, chromStart/chromEnd will be used (like R).
//
// This is a faithful port, not a re-design.
// NOTE/WARNING: This code was generated by AI (ChatGPT) as a port from the R
// equivalent (make_final_table.R) in 2026 by Nadia Davidson.
// Code was thoroughly tested, but there may be difference

